fects%20a%20person%E2%80%99s%20thoughts%2C%20emotions%2C%20and%20behaviours.%20It%20involves%20psychotic%20symptoms%20like%20hallucinations%2C%20delusions%2C%20disorganised%20thinking%2C%20social%20withdrawal%2C%20and%20flattened%20affect.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20schizophrenia%2C%20the%20core%20disturbance%20is%20in%20reality%20orientation%2C%20the%20person%20often%20loses%20touch%20with%20reality.%20This%20impaired%20reality%20testing%20is%20a%20key%20feature%2C%20and%20it%20can%20affect%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3D%5C%229253875046%5C%22%20data-ad-client%3D%5C%22ca-pub-5691287967087057%5C%22%20data-ad-format%3D%5C%22fluid%5C%22%20data-ad-layout%3D%5C%22in-article%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cul%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ETime%20orientation%20(confused%20about%20day%2Ftime)%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPlace%20orientation%20(unsure%20where%20they%20are)%2C%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPerson%20orientation%20(mistrust%20or%20misidentification%20of%20others)%2C%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESituation%20orientation%20(misinterpreting%20context%2C%20such%20as%20thinking%20they%20are%20in%20danger%20when%20they%20are%20not)%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20Dissociative%20Identity%20Disorder%20(DID)%2C%20which%20people%20mistakenly%20refer%20to%20as%20%E2%80%9Csplit%20personality%E2%80%9D%2C%20involves%20two%20or%20more%20distinct%20identities%20or%20personality%20states%20that%20alternate%20in%20controlling%20the%20individual%E2%80%99s%20behavior.%20%E2%80%9CSo%2C%20schizophrenia%20is%20not%20about%20%E2%80%98having%20two%20minds.%E2%80%99%20It%E2%80%99s%20about%20a%20disruption%20in%20perceiving%20and%20processing%20reality.%20That%20distinction%20is%20crucial%20for%20both%20clinical%20understanding%20and%20reducing%20stigma%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3C