n%20in%20films%20or%20TV.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20confusion%20isn%E2%80%99t%20just%20a%20harmless%20mix-up%20%E2%80%94%20it%20changes%20how%20we%20see%20people.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20people%20think%20%E2%80%98split%20personality%2C%E2%80%99%20they%20assume%20instability%20or%20danger%2C%20and%20that%20makes%20stigma%20worse%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dr.%20Khanna%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3D%5C%227521127830%5C%22%20data-ad-client%3D%5C%22ca-pub-5691287967087057%5C%22%20data-ad-format%3D%5C%22fluid%5C%22%20data-ad-layout%3D%5C%22in-article%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20that%20stigma%20can%20be%20damaging.%20It%20can%20isolate%20people%2C%20prevent%20them%20from%20seeking%20help%2C%20and%20deepen%20the%20fear%20around%20something%20that%E2%80%99s%20already%20misunderstood.%20Understanding%20the%20difference%20is%20the%20first%20step%20to%20treating%20people%20with%20empathy%2C%20not%20fear.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EMyth%202%3A%20%E2%80%9CPeople%20with%20schizophrenia%20are%20always%20dangerous%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMovies%20often%20show%20people%20with%20schizophrenia%20as%20violent%20or%20unpredictable%20%E2%80%94%20someone%20lashing%20out%2C%20losing%20control%2C%20or%20whispering%20to%20themselves%20before%20doing%20something%20terrifying.%20But%20real%20life%20is%20very%20different.%20In%20reality%2C%20schizophrenia%20often%20looks%20quieter%2C%20more%20inward%2C%20and%20far%20more%20complex.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImagine%20someone%20who%20spends%20their%20afternoons%20sketching%2C%20listening%20to%20music%2C%20and%20helping%20around%20the%20house.%20They%E2%80%99re%20gentle%2C%20kind%2C%20and%20perhaps%20a%20little%20withdrawn.%20On%20some%20days%2C%20they%20might%20seem%20distant%20or%20distracted%20%E2%80%94%20maybe%20they%E2%80%99re%20hearing%20a%20voice%20no%20one%20else%20can%20hear%20or%20feel%20convinced%20that%20people%20are%20watching%20them%2C%20whispering%20things%20that%20aren%E2%80%99t%20really%20being%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3D%5C%229669016977%5C%22%20data-ad-client%3D%5C%22ca-pub-5691287967087057%5C%22%20data-ad-format%3D%5C%22fluid%5C%22%20data-ad-layout%3D%5C%22in-article%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20you%E2%80%99re%20seeing%20isn%E2%80%99t%20danger.%20You%E2%80%99re%20seeing%20someone%20trying%20to%20make%20sense%20of%20a%20world%20that%20suddenly%20feels%20unfamiliar%20or%20overwhelming.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHallucinations%20are%20when%20someone%20hears%2C%20sees%2C%20or%20feels%20something%20that%20isn%E2%80%99t%20really%20there.%20Delusions%20are%20fixed%20false%20beliefs%2C%20like%20thinking%20people%20are%20trying%20to%20harm%20you%2C%20or%20that%20you%20have%20extraordinary%20powers%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dr.%20Khanna%20explained.%20%E2%80%9CThese%20symptoms%20are%20different%20for%20each%20person%20and%20don%E2%80%99t%20make%20someone%20dangerous.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F136309%2Fmental-health-stigma-taboos-depression%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eindividuals%20with%20schizophrenia%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20vulnerable%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20harm%20than%20to%20cause%20it.%20Many%20live%20with%20fear%2C%20confusion%2C%20or%20distress%2C%20not%20aggression.%20The%20assumption%20that%20someone%20with%20schizophrenia%20is%20unsafe%20often%20leads%20to%20isolation%20and%20shame%2C%20making%20recovery%20even%20harder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EMyth%203%3A%20%E2%80%9CThey%20can%E2%80%99t%20live%20normal%20lives%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20diagnosis%20of%20schizophrenia%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20life%20stops.%20With%20access%20to%20the%20right%20care%2C%20many%20people%20continue%20to%20work%2C%20build%20relationships%2C%20raise%20families%2C%20and%20live%20independently.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20entirely%20possible%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Dr.%20Khanna.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20the%20key%20is%20consistent%20treatment%2C%20which%20includes%20regular%20medication%2C%20therapy%2C%20and%20strong%20support%20from%20family%20or%20caregivers.%E2%80%9D%20She%20emphasises%20that%20schizophrenia%20requires%20ongoing%20care%2C%20and%20stopping%20treatment%20abruptly%20can%20lead%20to%20relapses.%20But%20stability%20and%20fulfilment%20are%20very%20much%20within%20reach.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99ve%20seen%20people%20return%20to%20jobs%2C%20reconnect%20with%20loved%20ones%2C%20and%20manage%20their%20symptoms%20effectively.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20hopeless.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F05%2FTBI-featured-image-14-1748005549.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Early%20trauma%2C%20emotional%20neglect%2C%20abuse%2C%20all%20can%20contribute%20to%20schizophrenia.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F05%2FTBI-featured-image-14-1748005549.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F05%2FTBI-featured-image-14-1748005549-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F05%2FTBI-featured-image-14-1748005549-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F05%2FTBI-featured-image-14-1748005549-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F05%2FTBI-featured-image-14-1748005549-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-437685%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EEarly%20trauma%2C%20emotional%20neglect%2C%20and%20abuse%20can%20all%20contribute%20to%20schizophrenia.%20Picture%20source%3A%20Shutterstock%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr.%20Sharma%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CSchizophrenia%20is%20not%20like%20a%20physical%20illness%20where%20we%20can%20always%20talk%20in%20terms%20of%20a%20full%20cure.%20Instead%2C%20it%20is%20managed%20through%20a%20long-term%20recovery%20model.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CRecovery%20means%20reduction%20of%20symptoms%2C%20improved%20functioning%2C%20and%20a%20return%20to%20meaningful%20life%20roles.%20Many%20individuals%20live%20independently%2C%20maintain%20jobs%2C%20and%20have%20fulfilling%20relationships.%20The%20earlier%20the%20intervention%2C%20the%20better%20the%20outcome.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EMyth%204%3A%20%E2%80%9CMedicines%20alone%20can%20fix%20it%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20medication%20plays%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20reducing%20symptoms%2C%20schizophrenia%20is%20not%20just%20a%20medical%20issue%3B%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20bio-psycho-social%20condition%2C%20says%20Dr.%20Khanna.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBiologically%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20chemical%20imbalance%20in%20the%20brain.%20Psychologically%2C%20factors%20like%20childhood%20trauma%20or%20poor%20coping%20mechanisms%20contribute.%20And%20socially%2C%20how%20families%20and%20communities%20treat%20the%20person%20plays%20a%20huge%20role.%E2%80%9D%20This%20means%20recovery%20needs%20more%20than%20pills.%20It%20needs%20psychotherapy%2C%20social%20support%2C%20family%20involvement%2C%20and%20community%20acceptance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20can%E2%80%99t%20just%20give%20someone%20medicine%20and%20leave%20them%20to%20figure%20out%20the%20rest.%20Healing%20is%20a%20holistic%20process.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F05%2Ffeatured-img-27_11zon-1748009141.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dr%20Sharma%20points%20out%20that%20in%20genetically%20vulnerable%20individuals%2C%20trauma%20can%20serve%20as%20a%20trigger%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F05%2Ffeatured-img-27_11zon-1748009141.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F05%2Ffeatured-img-27_11zon-1748009141-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F05%2Ffeatured-img-27_11zon-1748009141-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F05%2Ffeatured-img-27_11zon-1748009141-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F05%2Ffeatured-img-27_11zon-1748009141-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-437820%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EDr%20Sharma%20points%20out%20that%20in%20genetically%20vulnerable%20individuals%2C%20trauma%20can%20serve%20as%20a%20trigger%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr.%20Sharma%20further%20explains%20the%20link%20between%20trauma%20and%20schizophrenia%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20schizophrenia%20is%20a%20neurodevelopmental%20disorder%20with%20biological%20roots%2C%20trauma%20acts%20as%20a%20major%20environmental%20risk%20factor%20that%20can%20influence%20both%20the%20onset%20and%20severity%20of%20symptoms.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEarly%20trauma%20disrupts%20brain%20development.%20Experiences%20like%20emotional%20neglect%2C%20abuse%2C%20or%20parental%20loss%20can%20alter%20brain%20pathways%20involved%20in%20stress%20and%20emotion%2C%20all%20of%20which%20are%20implicated%20in%20schizophrenia%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20points%20out%20that%20in%20genetically%20vulnerable%20individuals%2C%20trauma%20can%20serve%20as%20a%20trigger.%20%E2%80%9CChronic%20trauma%20may%20affect%20self-concept%20and%20social%20trust%2C%20leading%20to%20isolation%20and%20emotional%20dysregulation%20%E2%80%94%20all%20of%20which%20can%20worsen%20or%20mimic%20psychotic%20symptoms.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F162770%2Ffacts-myths-psychiatric-medication-mental-health%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERecognising%20and%20addressing%20trauma%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20stresses%2C%20is%20vital%20for%20holistic%2C%20person-centred%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20recovery%20often%20involves%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%A2%20Medication%20(primarily%20antipsychotics)%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%A2%20Psychotherapy%20(especially%20CBT%20for%20psychosis)%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%A2%20Social%20skills%20training%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%A2%20Family%20support%20and%20psychoeducation%2C%20and%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%A2%20Rehabilitation%20services%20(vocational%20and%20community%20support).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EMyth%205%3A%20%E2%80%9CThey%E2%80%99ll%20never%20get%20better%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20belief%20can%20be%20especially%20harmful%2C%20and%20simply%20isn%E2%80%99t%20true.%20While%20schizophrenia%20is%20a%20chronic%20condition%2C%20many%20people%20improve%20significantly%20over%20time%20with%20the%20right%20combination%20of%20care%20and%20support.%20Some%20achieve%20what%20doctors%20call%20%E2%80%9Cfunctional%20recovery%E2%80%9D%2C%20where%20they%20can%20manage%20symptoms%20and%20live%20full%2C%20independent%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20wish%20more%20people%20understood%20that%20schizophrenia%20isn%E2%80%99t%20the%20end%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Dr.%20Khanna.%20%E2%80%9CYes%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20long%20journey.%20But%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20journey%20people%20can%20walk%20and%20thrive%20through%2C%20if%20they%E2%80%99re%20supported.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr.%20Sharma%20echoes%20this%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20society%20understands%20that%20schizophrenia%20is%20not%20about%20demons%20or%20split%20minds%2C%20but%20a%20treatable%20condition%2C%20we%20can%20build%20systems%20that%20offer%20real%20hope.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EChanging%20the%20way%20we%20see%20schizophrenia%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20danger%20of%20misinformation%20isn%E2%80%99t%20just%20confusion%20%E2%80%94%20it%E2%80%99s%20neglect%2C%20discrimination%2C%20and%20delayed%20care.%20Across%20India%2C%20an%20estimated%203%20in%20every%201%2C000%20people%20live%20with%20schizophrenia%2C%20according%20to%20the%20National%20Mental%20Health%20Survey%20(2015%E2%80%9316).%20That%E2%80%99s%20over%204%20million%20people%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20never%20receive%20a%20formal%20diagnosis%20or%20access%20to%20consistent%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20availability%20of%20treatment%20options%2C%20nearly%2075%25%20of%20people%20with%20severe%20mental%20disorders%20in%20India%2C%20including%20schizophrenia%2C%20do%20not%20receive%20any%20mental%20health%20care%2C%20as%20highlighted%20by%20the%20World%20Health%20Organisation%20(WHO).%20Often%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20the%20illness%20itself%20but%20the%20fear%2C%20silence%2C%20and%20stigma%20surrounding%20it%20that%20keep%20people%20from%20reaching%20out%20for%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F05%2Ffeatured-img-28_11zon-1748009317.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%20While%20schizophrenia%20is%20a%20chronic%20condition%2C%20many%20people%20improve%20significantly%20over%20time%20with%20the%20right%20combination%20of%20care%20and%20support.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F05%2Ffeatured-img-28_11zon-1748009317.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F05%2Ffeatured-img-28_11zon-1748009317-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F05%2Ffeatured-img-28_11zon-1748009317-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F05%2Ffeatured-img-28_11zon-1748009317-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F05%2Ffeatured-img-28_11zon-1748009317-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-437830%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%20While%20schizophrenia%20is%20a%20chronic%20condition%2C%20many%20people%20improve%20significantly%20over%20time%20with%20the%20right%20combination%20of%20care%20and%20support.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBehind%20every%20missed%20diagnosis%20is%20someone%20trying%20to%20cope%20%E2%80%94%20often%20alone%20%E2%80%94%20while%20the%20world%20looks%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20change%20starts%20with%20awareness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20need%20to%20stop%20seeing%20people%20with%20schizophrenia%20as%20their%20diagnosis%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Dr.%20Khanna.%20%E2%80%9CThey%E2%80%99re%20individuals%20%E2%80%94%20with%20strengths%2C%20stories%2C%20families%2C%20and%20dreams.%20If%20we%20shift%20our%20approach%2C%20we%20can%20change%20their%20lives.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20breaking%20the%20myths%2C%20opening%20up%20conversations%2C%20and%20replacing%20judgement%20with%20empathy%2C%20we%20can%20help%20more%20people%20find%20not%20just%20treatment%2C%20but%20dignity%2C%20purpose%2C%20and%20belonging.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20journey%20toward%20understanding%20schizophrenia%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20end%20with%20reading%20an%20article.%20It%20begins%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELearn%20the%20difference%20between%20fact%20and%20fiction.%20Listen%20to%20lived%20experiences.%20Talk%20to%20someone.%20Support%20organisations%20working%20in%20the%20mental%20health%20space.%20Small%2